body_html:
It looks like the only quantized model we have available is this one:
http://download.tensorflow.org/models/mobilenet_v1_1.0_224_quantized_frozen.tgz

Non-quantized models are available for all other sizes (as described in retrain.py). E.g. the non-quantized version of 1.0_160 is available:
http://download.tensorflow.org/models/mobilenet_v1_1.0_160_frozen.tgz

This corresponds to the following argument to retrain.py:

--architecture mobilenet_1.0_160

@suharshs might have more details on whether we plan to make more quantized models available.

body:
It looks like the only quantized model we have available is this one:
http://download.tensorflow.org/models/mobilenet_v1_1.0_224_quantized_frozen.tgz

Non-quantized models are available for all other sizes (as described in `retrain.py`).  E.g. the non-quantized version of 1.0_160 is available:
http://download.tensorflow.org/models/mobilenet_v1_1.0_160_frozen.tgz

This corresponds to the following argument to `retrain.py`:
```
--architecture mobilenet_1.0_160
```

@suharshs might have more details on whether we plan to make more quantized models available.
